    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-04-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="436"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord
                        Lyons</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-04-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 1, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: Referring to your memorandum of the 19th
                    ultimo, calling attention to the General Order of the War Department, (No. 82,)
                    of the 21st of July, 1862, concerning the administration of oaths to aliens, and
                    to my reply, I now have <pb facs="0578" n="536" xml:id="pg_536"/> the honor to
                    inform you that, from information recently received from that department, it
                    appears that directions have been given to the Adjutant General to comply with
                    your suggestions on the subject.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be your very obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
